Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.15,0:00:03.99,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A racing second hand, a shooting comet!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.99,0:00:07.46,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Conan's logic is good medicine\Nfor hearts tired by modern society!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.46,0:00:10.93,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today's case is animal protection!\NFolk tales have deep meanings!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.93,0:00:12.53,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.53,0:00:14.57,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.57,0:00:16.85,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.89,0:01:47.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you really sure this is the road?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.99,0:01:51.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! They should be in the marsh just ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.73,0:01:58.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ugh. Here we are in Hokkaido,\Nso why no crabs or hot springs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.37,0:02:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can see cranes at the zoo any old time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.34,0:02:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Red-crowned cranes are a protected species and only found in Hokkaido!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.41,0:02:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.42,0:02:16.38,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)}Feeding Ground
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.63,0:02:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another one is flying! How cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.00,0:02:31.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are we done yet? We gotta find a place to stay,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.77,0:02:33.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,or we'll be sleeping in the car tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.77,0:02:35.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.04,0:02:40.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who gave you permission to be here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.31,0:02:43.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Permission? Is this private property?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.51,0:02:44.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.78,0:02:46.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.05,0:02:50.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard red-crowned cranes don't like people, so we came here to watch them...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.52,0:02:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hope you're not crane thieves...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.72,0:02:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do I look like that kind of person?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.73,0:02:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.19,0:02:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, why is this window made of tempered glass?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.43,0:03:02.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the same kind used in planes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.47,0:03:05.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some people like to break windows for fun...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.87,0:03:07.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you like the red-crowned cranes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.20,0:03:08.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Yes!\N- Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.68,0:03:16.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's so fun about taking care of cranes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.55,0:03:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Old people make no sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.45,0:03:22.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad! He asked if we'd stay the night!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.92,0:03:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's even an open-air bath nearby!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.82,0:03:31.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} did help me,\Nand the red-crowned cranes are overjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.43,0:03:33.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's our way of saying thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.33,0:03:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that mean... it's free?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.70,0:03:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave if you don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.90,0:03:40.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing of the sort! We'd be glad to stay!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.54,0:03:42.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the cranes' return favor!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.04,0:03:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.94,0:03:45.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That there is my home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.41,0:03:47.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I live alone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.38,0:03:55.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your wife passed away five years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.69,0:03:58.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've lived all alone ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.62,0:04:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This thing looks alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.79,0:04:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I stuff red-crowned cranes\Nthat die from injuries or illness
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.96,0:04:08.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and donate them to schools and museums.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.40,0:04:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello, there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.60,0:04:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is my brother, Tamotsu.\NHe started sponging off me 10 days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.74,0:04:16.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a worthless painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.31,0:04:18.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't need the "worthless" part, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.88,0:04:23.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just told the truth. You lack observational skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.01,0:04:25.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's your fatal flaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.45,0:04:28.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This here is Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.25,0:04:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.10,0:04:34.44,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Machida Tamotsu (53)\NPainter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective? Are you the famous Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.93,0:04:39.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My reputation's even made it to Hokkaido, has it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.13,0:04:40.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.60,0:04:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.26,0:04:43.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tamotsu is from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.55,0:04:44.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.70,0:04:48.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this tempered glass for, Mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.07,0:04:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to use it in that window, so I can watch the red-crowned cranes from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.45,0:05:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.66,0:05:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.89,0:05:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you two here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.79,0:05:08.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you really donating your estate to the village?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.16,0:05:09.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not true, is it, Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.86,0:05:10.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.96,0:05:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want it to take care of the red-crowned cranes and other migratory birds forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.19,0:05:23.19,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Noriko Machida (29)\NBoutique Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.19,0:05:23.19,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hiroshi Machida (27)\NOffice Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.33,0:05:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! What about taking care of me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.00,0:05:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad! Help me! My boutique's going to be taken over!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.07,0:05:26.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quit it! We have company!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.88,0:05:30.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn! All any of you want is money, money, money!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.62,0:05:34.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, we're family!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.02,0:05:36.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, why isn't there a fire going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.70,0:05:38.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't, Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.15,0:05:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Eh?\N- Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.69,0:05:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.43,0:05:46.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A turtledove made its nest on the chimney last spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.63,0:05:48.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's since left it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.77,0:05:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She might come back this spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.40,0:05:56.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not to touch anything in this house, not just the fireplace!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.74,0:06:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Birds, birds, birds! Are birds more important than your own children?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:03.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a great parent!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.31,0:06:06.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tamotsu, did you call these two here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.42,0:06:09.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I knew you wouldn't like it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.99,0:06:15.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I felt it was best to discuss this sooner rather than later...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.13,0:06:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How egotistical.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.13,0:06:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your Uncle Tamotsu probably told you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.13,0:06:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but an attorney is bringing the form here at 5:00 today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.67,0:06:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The minute I stamp it, my 300 million will go to the village once I die!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.31,0:06:31.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}300 million?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.24,0:06:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'll talk with that attorney!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.41,0:06:36.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,300 million for red-crowned cranes?!\NYou're out of your mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.68,0:06:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no point!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.32,0:06:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already given you your amount of inheritance required by law!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.69,0:06:45.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You haven't been here in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.26,0:06:49.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't hurt to visit your mother's grave!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.83,0:06:53.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn him! Now what do we do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.10,0:06:56.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll talk to the attorney! I will put an end to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.47,0:07:01.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Geez. This is some place we wound up staying at...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.61,0:07:07.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll be all better soon! Just hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.18,0:07:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used to be a CEO?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.45,0:07:13.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He had a car dealership in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.45,0:07:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister fell ill 8 years ago and moved here with him to recuperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.16,0:07:24.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just the two of them? What about their kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.29,0:07:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Noriko and Hiroshi didn't want to leave Tokyo,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.76,0:07:32.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so my brother gave them their inheritance early.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.34,0:07:36.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they used it all up? I'm so jealous...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.02,0:07:49.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop! What're you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.02,0:07:53.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quiet! It ain't loaded! Or are you blind?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.82,0:07:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.50,0:08:02.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a horrible son.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.60,0:08:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm alive again...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.97,0:08:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, there's something missing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.81,0:08:17.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've got a bad feeling about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.48,0:08:25.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Geez! Get your own {\i1}sake{\i0}, will ya?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.79,0:08:28.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.20,0:08:37.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That hits the spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.40,0:08:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?\NIsn't it a great hot spring?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.00,0:08:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The best! No complaints from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.64,0:08:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Glad to hear it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.10,0:08:46.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.24,0:08:52.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I've been here for 10 days,\Nbut my sketchbook is still blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.28,0:08:55.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thought I'd head to the feeding ground\Nto sketch some red-crowned cranes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.42,0:08:58.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, enjoy yourselves—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.59,0:08:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.35,0:09:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.69,0:09:04.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. I'll stop by again at around 5:00 when the attorney arrives,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.69,0:09:07.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so please enjoy yourselves until then!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.16,0:09:10.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure! I'll enjoy myself plenty!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.27,0:09:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad! You should get out before he gets here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.94,0:09:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not yet! There's no telling when I'll get to visit another hot spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.51,0:09:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's your own fault if you wind up fainting!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.89,0:09:34.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}... Is he going back to Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.23,0:09:39.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So dizzy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.66,0:09:42.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't you ever heard of limits?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.90,0:09:44.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't feel so good...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.73,0:09:46.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Of course you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.00,0:09:49.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You were in there for 2 hours\Nand swam after drinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.41,0:09:51.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is he all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.91,0:09:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's just dizzy! Anyways, did you get any drawings done?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.05,0:09:59.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep. As you can see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.85,0:10:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! You're really good!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.52,0:10:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I should be going back. Take your time, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.36,0:10:11.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.61,0:10:20.99,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo Yamagami (58)\NAttorney
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.17,0:10:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Evening, Tamotsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Is Shuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} home?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.99,0:10:25.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he should be waiting for you. Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.39,0:10:37.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The window's broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.46,0:10:43.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.36,0:10:45.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.00,0:10:52.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No good! It's locked from the inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.80,0:10:54.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.34,0:10:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My brother's been killed with an arrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.37,0:11:01.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.48,0:11:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.25,0:11:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.42,0:11:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle! Hiroshi ran off!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.82,0:11:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calm down, Nori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.29,0:11:19.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You look for Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! I'll tell Detective Mouri at the hot spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.16,0:11:21.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You call the police with the phone by the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.86,0:11:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.94,0:11:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the crossbow was shot from outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.71,0:11:37.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The window is locked, and the door was locked from the inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.08,0:11:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. He always locks it at 4:00 to watch his videos.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.12,0:11:45.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would watch videos of my late sister every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.79,0:11:52.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably didn't want anyone to see him visiting her...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.73,0:11:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, he had the windows made of ground glass?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.33,0:11:59.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was about to put in tempered glass so he could finally
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.54,0:12:03.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,get over the sadness and watch his red-crowned cranes whenever he wanted...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.87,0:12:07.81,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But he was murdered just before he could...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.81,0:12:09.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's a mark on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.95,0:12:13.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The arrow was shot from this window?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.15,0:12:16.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.92,0:12:19.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why are the shards all lined up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.99,0:12:22.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And there's another mark on the floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.83,0:12:23.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Tamotsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.89,0:12:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.85,0:12:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't find him anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.00,0:12:27.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And our car is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.90,0:12:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We saw Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} drive off just after 5:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.90,0:12:33.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd he seem?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.10,0:12:36.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He seemed in a real hurry...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.21,0:12:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.11,0:12:42.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Soot?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.08,0:12:47.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's soot gone in some places!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.29,0:12:51.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An unburned wood chip?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.85,0:12:52.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.99,0:12:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No nosing around the crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.00,0:13:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.65,0:13:06.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.82,0:13:11.33,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Detective Ezomatsu\NHokkai Police Department
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.90,0:13:09.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Ezomatsu, of the Hokkai Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.04,0:13:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This man has confessed to killing his father with this crossbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.41,0:13:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Confessed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.24,0:13:16.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.45,0:13:21.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the famous Tokyo detective, Kogoro Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.15,0:13:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Famous detective? Mouri what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.75,0:13:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kogoro...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.46,0:13:29.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Guess my name really hasn't spread to Hokkaido...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.99,0:13:31.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.46,0:13:34.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What is it?! Something's not right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.50,0:13:41.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just meant to scare him, not kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.54,0:13:45.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I aimed for that stuffed red-crowned crane...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.94,0:13:49.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought if I scared him,\Nhe wouldn't donate his fortune away...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.95,0:13:53.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you took the crossbow from the workshop?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.95,0:13:56.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I peeked inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.32,0:13:59.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw him on the sofa, watching a video of Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.39,0:14:05.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I aimed at the red-crowned crane,\Ntook two steps back, and shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.53,0:14:09.49,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That scare ya?! Next time it won't be a—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.57,0:14:14.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.50,0:14:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But my sister kept telling me to!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.61,0:14:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! I never said to kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.91,0:14:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that was only because Uncle Tamotsu said
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.31,0:14:26.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad might change his mind if we really scared him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.48,0:14:30.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, Nori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! I would never say anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.82,0:14:33.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There must be some misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.89,0:14:38.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A feather in his back pocket...\NIs it a red-crowned crane feather?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.83,0:14:40.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Feather?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.27,0:14:49.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I thought so! But, this isn't enough to—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.84,0:14:52.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait! The skylight!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.42,0:15:03.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yes! I found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.05,0:15:05.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The peculiar red-crowned crane sketches...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.32,0:15:07.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The mark on the tempered glass...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.19,0:15:10.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The lined-up glass shards and mark on the floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.43,0:15:12.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And, the wood chip in the fireplace!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.66,0:15:15.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}One thing connected them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.06,0:15:16.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} isn't the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.21,0:15:24.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Believe me! I really didn't mean to kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.91,0:15:29.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, alright. We can continue this discussion back at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.58,0:15:35.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, I must ask you to come as well.\NYou're suspected of abetting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.65,0:15:37.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.25,0:15:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That alright with you, Mr. Famous Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.46,0:15:46.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course! After all, he himself confessed to the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.23,0:15:49.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mosquito this time of year...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.77,0:15:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not so fast, Detective Ezomatsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.50,0:15:57.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did not murder Shuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.14,0:16:01.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of nonsense is this?\NHe's already admitted to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.48,0:16:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how do you explain\Nthe glass shards his arrow made?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.72,0:16:10.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Glass shards?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.29,0:16:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These? What about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.49,0:16:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you find it odd?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.49,0:16:16.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The arrow was shot from outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.36,0:16:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the resulting glass shards are all lined up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.73,0:16:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is why I don't like amateurs,\Nthey tamper with crime scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.37,0:16:27.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was something lying here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.94,0:16:31.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! The tempered glass had been placed there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.88,0:16:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tempered glass?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.21,0:16:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.18,0:16:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, just like that, Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fired the crossbow from outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.22,0:16:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then the glass shards fell to the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.99,0:16:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.33,0:16:54.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on! Wouldn't the arrow hit the tempered glass, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.20,0:16:59.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The arrow hit the glass and struck the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.87,0:17:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As tempered glass is clear,\NHiroshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't notice from outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.81,0:17:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then where did the arrow in the victim's chest come from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.05,0:17:16.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From inside the fireplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.39,0:17:19.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside it is a part with soot removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.92,0:17:23.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because a crossbow had been set up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.69,0:17:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how was it shot from inside here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.36,0:17:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.80,0:17:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was lying inside the fireplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.97,0:17:33.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's a wood chip got to do with anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.30,0:17:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, you stick a wood chip with a string around it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.97,0:17:39.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,behind the trigger of the crossbow in the fireplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.94,0:17:44.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, you attach a strip of rubber around the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.12,0:17:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The string tied to the wood chip is led up the chimney and outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.19,0:17:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person with that string then looked through the skylight
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.96,0:17:57.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and checked that Shuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was sitting in his usual spot...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.66,0:18:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then pulled the string\Njust as Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fired his crossbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.50,0:18:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That arrow struck Shuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in the chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.37,0:18:10.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The string left distinct marks inside the chimney.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.81,0:18:17.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The arrow had fireplace soot on it,\Nso analysis should confirm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.28,0:18:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was a premeditated murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.53,0:18:22.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. A carefully premeditated one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.59,0:18:27.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the killer took care of the glass and crossbow after the murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.69,0:18:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} couldn't have done it, he had run off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.33,0:18:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, he's not the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.23,0:18:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who murdered Shuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and cleared away the glass\Nand crossbow in this locked room...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.07,0:18:43.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was you, Tamotsu Machida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.77,0:18:47.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, three people were at the scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.51,0:18:50.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They would've noticed the tempered glass had been moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.88,0:18:52.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.08,0:18:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first thing most people at a crime scene notice
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.09,0:18:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.69,0:19:01.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By quickly forcing them back into the hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.26,0:19:04.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they wouldn't be able to recall the condition of the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.20,0:19:08.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, you gave them orders to leave the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.77,0:19:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, you took care of the tempered glass and crossbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.47,0:19:16.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your reason for murdering Shuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.81,0:19:20.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was likely because he refused to loan you money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.28,0:19:23.68,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn! All any of you want is money, money, money!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.68,0:19:29.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't say that in regard to just them, but to you as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.45,0:19:34.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you lured them here, into a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.53,0:19:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, you wouldn't get any inheritance if you killed him yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.23,0:19:45.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, but when my brother was murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.90,0:19:50.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was at the feeding ground drawing pictures, as you can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.01,0:19:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason I suspected you was because of those drawings!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.95,0:19:59.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason being that red-crowned cranes' tails aren't black!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.65,0:20:04.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their plumes are black, and their tails are white!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.09,0:20:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, red-crowned cranes face the wind when they sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.09,0:20:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, they're sleeping against the wind in your drawings.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.33,0:20:16.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because you didn't draw them at the feeding ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.10,0:20:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you drew this stuffed one instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.44,0:20:22.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably several days earlier, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.61,0:20:26.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make us think you drew them today,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.18,0:20:30.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you showed us an unused sketchbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.55,0:20:32.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.68,0:20:37.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true, I might've drawn their feathers incorrectly,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.55,0:20:42.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but you haven't proven I didn't draw these there, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.89,0:20:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember when you dropped your sketchbook at the hot spring?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.73,0:20:53.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you did, Conan caught it\Nand gave it back to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.74,0:20:58.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Conan's fingerprints should be on your sketchbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.64,0:21:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Assuming it's the same one, that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.25,0:21:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wiped it down when it got dirty later!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.65,0:21:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well. The proof is the feather in your back pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.89,0:21:12.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A red-crowned crane feather...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.79,0:21:17.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's not a red-crowned crane feather.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.19,0:21:21.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a feather of the turtledove\Nthat made a nest atop the chimney.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.93,0:21:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It probably got there when you stuffed the string in your pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.97,0:21:33.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ergo, there should be soot in your pocket, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.48,0:21:40.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unbelievable. Being suspected because of my drawings...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.82,0:21:45.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I never did have any artistic talent...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.26,0:21:49.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like my brother said, I lack observational skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.46,0:21:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've finally realized it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.70,0:23:24.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Entire Fortune Donated! Migratory Bird Foundation Created"...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.97,0:23:29.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it's great that his children decided to follow in his footsteps
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.27,0:23:31.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and take care of the red-crowned cranes...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.48,0:23:34.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But 300 million?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.15,0:23:37.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanna be a red-crowned crane\Nand get taken care of...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.05,0:23:43.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This guy never changes his ways...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.42,0:23:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most of Mr. Torakura's novels feature vampires,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.80,0:23:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so his nickname is "Mr. Dracula".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.34,0:24:04.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the windows were locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.04,0:24:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.48,0:24:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is an insider!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.03,0:24:14.07,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.07,0:24:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Film Projector
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.08,0:24:20.60,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time... What crosses your mind when I say Dracula?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.60,0:24:21.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,A cross!
